hm2IOModuleMib.name: hm2IOModuleMib
hm2IOModuleMib.contactinfo: Postal: Stuttgarter Str. 45-51 72654 Neckartenzlingen Germany Phone: +49 7127 140 E-mail: hac.support@belden.com

hm2IOModConfigDigInputAdminState.name: hm2IOModConfigDigInputAdminState
hm2IOModConfigDigInputAdminState.description: Enables polling of input values. (if disable(2) input task will do nothing)

hm2IOModConfigDigOutputAdminState.name: hm2IOModConfigDigOutputAdminState
hm2IOModConfigDigOutputAdminState.description: Enables mirroring of input values to output ports. (if disable(2) output task will do nothing)

hm2IOModConfigDigInputRefreshInterval.name: hm2IOModConfigDigInputRefreshInterval
hm2IOModConfigDigInputRefreshInterval.description: The refresh interval (in ms) of the input values. The accuracy of the interval value is 100ms. Minimum 1000ms (1s), Maximum 10000ms (10s).

hm2IOModConfigDigOutputRefreshInterval.name: hm2IOModConfigDigOutputRefreshInterval
hm2IOModConfigDigOutputRefreshInterval.description: The refresh interval (in ms) of the output values. The accuracy of the interval value is 100ms. Minimum 1000ms (1s), Maximum 10000ms (10s).

hm2IOModConfigDigOutputRetryCount.name: hm2IOModConfigDigOutputRetryCount
hm2IOModConfigDigOutputRetryCount.description: The retry count for the output values. when after the number of configured retries no SNMP get request was answered, the output value (hm2IOModValueDigOutputValue) will be set to invalid (3). Minimum 1, Maximum 10.

hm2IOModConfigDigInputTable.name: hm2IOModConfigDigInputTable
hm2IOModConfigDigInputTable.description: IO module config table for inputs

hm2IOModConfigDigInputEntry.name: hm2IOModConfigDigInputEntry
hm2IOModConfigDigInputEntry.description: IO module config entry for inputs

hm2IOModConfigDigInputModID.name: hm2IOModConfigDigInputModID
hm2IOModConfigDigInputModID.description: The module ID of an input. Module ID 0 corresponds to the power supply module.

hm2IOModConfigDigInputLogEvent.name: hm2IOModConfigDigInputLogEvent
hm2IOModConfigDigInputLogEvent.description: Trigger an event log when input status changes. If the value is disable (2), no event log entry will be written. If the value is enable (1), an event log entry will be written when the input state changes. The input state will be checked according to the refresh interval entered in hm2IOModConfigDigInputRefreshInterval.

hm2IOModConfigDigInputSnmpTrap.name: hm2IOModConfigDigInputSnmpTrap
hm2IOModConfigDigInputSnmpTrap.description: Trigger an SNMP trap log when input status changes. If the value is disable (2), no SNMP trap will be sent. If the value is enable (1), a SNMP trap will be sent when the input state changes. The SNMP trap will be sent to all receivers configured in the snmpTargetAddrTable. The input state will be checked according to the refresh interval entered in hm2IOModConfigDigInputRefreshInterval.

hm2IOModConfigDigOutputTable.name: hm2IOModConfigDigOutputTable
hm2IOModConfigDigOutputTable.description: IO module config table for outputs.

hm2IOModConfigDigOutputEntry.name: hm2IOModConfigDigOutputEntry
hm2IOModConfigDigOutputEntry.description: IO module config entry for outputs

hm2IOModConfigDigOutputModID.name: hm2IOModConfigDigOutputModID
hm2IOModConfigDigOutputModID.description: The module ID of an output. Module ID 0 corresponds to the power supply module.

hm2IOModConfigDigOutputLogEvent.name: hm2IOModConfigDigOutputLogEvent
hm2IOModConfigDigOutputLogEvent.description: Trigger an event log when output status changes. If the value is disable (2), no event log entry will be written. If the value is enable (1), an event log entry will be written when the output state changes. The output state will be checked according to the refresh interval entered in hm2IOModConfigDigOutputRefreshInterval.

hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSnmpTrap.name: hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSnmpTrap
hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSnmpTrap.description: Trigger an SNMP trap log when output status changes. If the value is disable (2), no SNMP trap will be sent. If the value is enable (1), a SNMP trap will be sent when the output state changes. The SNMP trap will be sent to all receivers configured in the snmpTargetAddrTable. The output state will be checked according to the refresh interval entered in hm2IOModConfigDigOutputRefreshInterval.

hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourceAddressType.name: hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourceAddressType
hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourceAddressType.description: Address type of an input mirrored to the output. Currently, only ipv4 is supported.

hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourceAddress.name: hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourceAddress
hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourceAddress.description: The IP address of an input mirrored to the output. Use 0.0.0.0 if the output should not be set. In this case hm2IOModValueDigOutputValue is not-configured(4). Use 127.0.0.1 if a local input should be used.

hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourcePort.name: hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourcePort
hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourcePort.description: The SNMP port number being used by the input mirrored to the output. This port would be the destination of the SNMP requests for polling the state of the input.

hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourceModID.name: hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourceModID
hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourceModID.description: The module ID of an input mirrored to the output. Module ID 0 corresponds to the power supply module. Ignored when hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourceIP is 0.0.0.0.

hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourceID.name: hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourceID
hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourceID.description: The ID of an input mirrored to the output. Ignored when hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSourceIP is 0.0.0.0.

hm2IOModValueDigInputTable.name: hm2IOModValueDigInputTable
hm2IOModValueDigInputTable.description: IO module value table for inputs

hm2IOModValueDigInputEntry.name: hm2IOModValueDigInputEntry
hm2IOModValueDigInputEntry.description: IO module value entry for inputs

hm2IOModValueDigInputModID.name: hm2IOModValueDigInputModID
hm2IOModValueDigInputModID.description: The module ID of an input. Module ID 0 corresponds to the power supply module.

hm2IOModValueDigInputValue.name: hm2IOModValueDigInputValue
hm2IOModValueDigInputValue.description: Status of the input. If the value is not-available(0), then the IO module is not plugged in, if the value is high(1), the input has high (+24V) value, if the value is low(2), the input has low (0V) value.

hm2IOModValueDigOutputTable.name: hm2IOModValueDigOutputTable
hm2IOModValueDigOutputTable.description: IO module value table for outputs

hm2IOModValueDigOutputEntry.name: hm2IOModValueDigOutputEntry
hm2IOModValueDigOutputEntry.description: IO module value entry for outputs

hm2IOModValueDigOutputModID.name: hm2IOModValueDigOutputModID
hm2IOModValueDigOutputModID.description: The module ID of an Output. Module ID 0 corresponds to the power supply module.

hm2IOModValueDigOutputValue.name: hm2IOModValueDigOutputValue
hm2IOModValueDigOutputValue.description: Status of the output. If the value is not-available(0), then the IO module is not plugged in, if the value is high(1), the output has high (+24V) value, if the value is low(2), the output has low (0V) value. If the value is invalid (3), the output has low (0V) value and the IO input source is configured but cannot be read. If the value is not-configured (4), the output has low (0V) value and has no IO input source configured.

hm2IOModDigInputChangeTrap.name: hm2IOModDigInputChangeTrap
hm2IOModDigInputChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent if the state of an input changes. This trap is sent only when hm2IOModConfigDigInputSnmpTrap is set to enabled (1).

hm2IOModDigOutputChangeTrap.name: hm2IOModDigOutputChangeTrap
hm2IOModDigOutputChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent if the state of an input changes. This trap is sent when hm2IOModConfigDigOutputSnmpTrap is set to enabled (1) or when the output value changes from or to invalid (3).
